data.name: h_desc
data.value: Either shows a help for a single command, or DMs you help link if no arguments are specified.

data.name: donate_desc
data.value: Instructions for helping the project financially.

data.name: commands_desc
data.value: List all of the bot's commands from a certain module. You can either specify the full name or only the first few letters of the module name.

data.name: greetdel_desc
data.value: Sets the time it takes (in seconds) for greet messages to be auto-deleted. Set it to 0 to disable automatic deletion.

data.name: greet_desc
data.value: Toggles anouncements on the current channel when someone joins the server.

data.name: greetmsg_desc
data.value: Sets a new join announcement message which will be shown in the server's channel. Type `%user%` if you want to mention the new member. Using it with no message will show the current greet message. You can use embed json from <http://nadekobot.me/embedbuilder/> instead of a regular text, if you want the message to be embedded.

data.name: bye_desc
data.value: Toggles anouncements on the current channel when someone leaves the server.

data.name: byemsg_desc
data.value: Sets a new leave announcement message. Type `%user%` if you want to show the name the user who left. Type `%id%` to show id. Using this command with no message will show the current bye message. You can use embed json from <http://nadekobot.me/embedbuilder/> instead of a regular text, if you want the message to be embedded.

data.name: byedel_desc
data.value: Sets the time it takes (in seconds) for bye messages to be auto-deleted. Set it to `0` to disable automatic deletion.

data.name: greetdm_desc
data.value: Toggles whether the greet messages will be sent in a DM (This is separate from greet - you can have both, any or neither enabled).

data.name: logserver_desc
data.value: Enables or Disables ALL log events. If enabled, all log events will log to this channel.

data.name: logignore_desc
data.value: Toggles whether the `.logserver` command ignores this channel. Useful if you have hidden admin channel and public log channel.

data.name: userpresence_desc
data.value: Starts logging to this channel when someone from the server goes online/offline/idle.

data.name: voicepresence_desc
data.value: Toggles logging to this channel whenever someone joins or leaves a voice channel you are currently in.

data.name: repeatinvoke_desc
data.value: Immediately shows the repeat message on a certain index and restarts its timer.

data.name: repeat_desc
data.value: Repeat a message every `X` minutes in the current channel. You can have up to 5 repeating messages on the server in total.

data.name: rotateplaying_desc
data.value: Toggles rotation of playing status of the dynamic strings you previously specified.

data.name: addplaying_desc
data.value: Adds a specified string to the list of playing strings to rotate. Supported placeholders: `%servers%`, `%users%`, `%playing%`, `%queued%`, `%time%`, `%shardid%`, `%shardcount%`, `%shardguilds%`.

data.name: listplaying_desc
data.value: Lists all playing statuses with their corresponding number.

data.name: removeplaying_desc
data.value: Removes a playing string on a given number.

data.name: slowmode_desc
data.value: Toggles slowmode. Disable by specifying no parameters. To enable, specify a number of messages each user can send, and an interval in seconds. For example 1 message every 5 seconds.

data.name: cleanvplust_desc
data.value: Deletes all text channels ending in `-voice` for which voicechannels are not found. Use at your own risk.

data.name: voiceplustext_desc
data.value: Creates a text channel for each voice channel only users in that voice channel can see. If you are server owner, keep in mind you will see them all the time regardless.

data.name: scsc_desc
data.value: Starts an instance of cross server channel. You will get a token as a DM that other people will use to tune in to the same instance.

data.name: jcsc_desc
data.value: Joins current channel to an instance of cross server channel using the token.

data.name: lcsc_desc
data.value: Leaves a cross server channel instance from this channel.

data.name: asar_desc
data.value: Adds a role to the list of self-assignable roles.

data.name: rsar_desc
data.value: Removes a specified role from the list of self-assignable roles.

data.name: tesar_desc
data.value: Toggles whether the self-assigned roles are exclusive. (So that any person can have only one of the self assignable roles)

data.name: iam_desc
data.value: Adds a role to you that you choose. Role must be on a list of self-assignable roles.

data.name: iamnot_desc
data.value: Removes a specified role from you. Role must be on a list of self-assignable roles.

data.name: addcustreact_desc
data.value: Add a custom reaction with a trigger and a response. Running this command in server requires the Administration permission. Running this command in DM is Bot Owner only and adds a new global custom reaction. Guide here: <http://nadekobot.readthedocs.io/en/latest/Custom%20Reactions/>

data.name: listcustreact_desc
data.value: Lists global or server custom reactions (20 commands per page). Running the command in DM will list global custom reactions, while running it in server will list that server's custom reactions. Specifying `all` argument instead of the number will DM you a text file with a list of all custom reactions.

data.name: listcustreactg_desc
data.value: Lists global or server custom reactions (20 commands per page) grouped by trigger, and show a number of responses for each. Running the command in DM will list global custom reactions, while running it in server will list that server's custom reactions.

data.name: showcustreact_desc
data.value: Shows a custom reaction's response on a given ID.

data.name: delcustreact_desc
data.value: Deletes a custom reaction on a specific index. If ran in DM, it is bot owner only and deletes a global custom reaction. If ran in a server, it requires Administration privileges and removes server custom reaction.

data.name: autoassignrole_desc
data.value: Automaticaly assigns a specified role to every user who joins the server.

data.name: autoassignrole_usage
data.value: `{0}aar` to disable, `{0}aar Role Name` to enable

data.name: leave_desc
data.value: Makes Nadeko leave the server. Either server name or server ID is required.

data.name: delmsgoncmd_desc
data.value: Toggles the automatic deletion of the user's successful command message to prevent chat flood.

data.name: restart_desc
data.value: Restarts the bot. Might not work.

data.name: setrole_desc
data.value: Sets a role for a given user.

data.name: removerole_desc
data.value: Removes a role from a given user.

data.name: renamerole_desc
data.value: Renames a role. The role you are renaming must be lower than bot's highest role.

data.name: removeallroles_desc
data.value: Removes all roles from a mentioned user.

data.name: createrole_desc
data.value: Creates a role with a given name.

data.name: rolecolor_desc
data.value: Set a role's color to the hex or 0-255 rgb color value provided.

data.name: ban_desc
data.value: Bans a user by ID or name with an optional message.

data.name: softban_desc
data.value: Bans and then unbans a user by ID or name with an optional message.

data.name: mute_desc
data.value: Mutes a mentioned user both from speaking and chatting. You can also specify time in minutes (up to 1440) for how long the user should be muted.

data.name: voiceunmute_desc
data.value: Gives a previously voice-muted user a permission to speak.

data.name: delvoichanl_desc
data.value: Deletes a voice channel with a given name.

data.name: creatvoichanl_desc
data.value: Creates a new voice channel with a given name.

data.name: deltxtchanl_desc
data.value: Deletes a text channel with a given name.

data.name: creatxtchanl_desc
data.value: Creates a new text channel with a given name.

data.name: settopic_desc
data.value: Sets a topic on the current channel.

data.name: setchanlname_desc
data.value: Changes the name of the current channel.

data.name: prune_desc
data.value: `{0}prune` removes all Nadeko's messages in the last 100 messages. `{0}prune X` removes last `X` number of messages from the channel (up to 100). `{0}prune @Someone` removes all Someone's messages in the last 100 messages. `{0}prune @Someone X` removes last `X` number of 'Someone's' messages in the channel.

data.name: setname_desc
data.value: Gives the bot a new name.

data.name: setavatar_desc
data.value: Sets a new avatar image for the NadekoBot. Argument is a direct link to an image.

data.name: send_desc
data.value: Sends a message to someone on a different server through the bot. Separate server and channel/user ids with `|` and prefix the channel id with `c:` and the user id with `u:`.

data.name: mentionrole_desc
data.value: Mentions every person from the provided role or roles (separated by a ',') on this server.

data.name: donators_desc
data.value: List of the lovely people who donated to keep this project alive.

data.name: donadd_desc
data.value: Add a donator to the database.

data.name: announce_desc
data.value: Sends a message to all servers' default channel that bot is connected to.

data.name: savechat_desc
data.value: Saves a number of messages to a text file and sends it to you.

data.name: remind_desc
data.value: Sends a message to you or a channel after certain amount of time. First argument is `me`/`here`/'channelname'. Second argument is time in a descending order (mo>w>d>h>m) example: 1w5d3h10m. Third argument is a (multiword) message.

data.name: remind_usage
data.value: `{0}remind me 1d5h Do something` or `{0}remind #general 1m Start now!`

data.name: remindtemplate_desc
data.value: Sets message for when the remind is triggered. Available placeholders are `%user%` - user who ran the command, `%message%` - Message specified in the remind, `%target%` - target channel of the remind.

data.name: serverinfo_desc
data.value: Shows info about the server the bot is on. If no channel is supplied, it defaults to current one.

data.name: channelinfo_desc
data.value: Shows info about the channel. If no channel is supplied, it defaults to current one.

data.name: userinfo_desc
data.value: Shows info about the user. If no user is supplied, it defaults a user running the command.

data.name: whosplaying_desc
data.value: Shows a list of users who are playing the specified game.

data.name: inrole_desc
data.value: Lists every person from the specified role on this server. You can use role ID, role name.

data.name: checkmyperms_desc
data.value: Checks your user-specific permissions on this channel.

data.name: stats_desc
data.value: Shows some basic stats for Nadeko.

data.name: roles_desc
data.value: List roles on this server or a roles of a specific user if specified. Paginated, 20 roles per page.

data.name: channeltopic_desc
data.value: Sends current channel's topic as a message.

data.name: chnlfilterinv_desc
data.value: Toggles automatic deletion of invites posted in the channel. Does not negate the `{0}srvrfilterinv` enabled setting. Does not affect the Bot Owner.

data.name: srvrfilterinv_desc
data.value: Toggles automatic deletion of invites posted in the server. Does not affect the Bot Owner.

data.name: chnlfilterwords_desc
data.value: Toggles automatic deletion of messages containing filtered words on the channel. Does not negate the `{0}srvrfilterwords` enabled setting. Does not affect the Bot Owner.

data.name: filterword_desc
data.value: Adds or removes (if it exists) a word from the list of filtered words. Use`{0}sfw` or `{0}cfw` to toggle filtering.

data.name: lstfilterwords_desc
data.value: Shows a list of filtered words.

data.name: srvrfilterwords_desc
data.value: Toggles automatic deletion of messages containing filtered words on the server. Does not affect the Bot Owner.

data.name: permrole_desc
data.value: Sets a role which can change permissions. Supply no parameters to see the current one. Default is 'Nadeko'.

data.name: verbose_desc
data.value: Sets whether to show when a command/module is blocked.

data.name: srvrmdl_desc
data.value: Sets a module's permission at the server level.

data.name: srvrcmd_desc
data.value: Sets a command's permission at the server level.

data.name: rolemdl_desc
data.value: Sets a module's permission at the role level.

data.name: rolecmd_desc
data.value: Sets a command's permission at the role level.

data.name: chnlmdl_desc
data.value: Sets a module's permission at the channel level.

data.name: chnlcmd_desc
data.value: Sets a command's permission at the channel level.

data.name: usrmdl_desc
data.value: Sets a module's permission at the user level.

data.name: usrcmd_desc
data.value: Sets a command's permission at the user level.

data.name: allsrvrmdls_desc
data.value: Enable or disable all modules for your server.

data.name: allchnlmdls_desc
data.value: Enable or disable all modules in a specified channel.

data.name: allrolemdls_desc
data.value: Enable or disable all modules for a specific role.

data.name: userblacklist_desc
data.value: Either [add]s or [rem]oves a user specified by a Mention or an ID from a blacklist.

data.name: channelblacklist_desc
data.value: Either [add]s or [rem]oves a channel specified by an ID from a blacklist.

data.name: serverblacklist_desc
data.value: Either [add]s or [rem]oves a server specified by a Name or an ID from a blacklist.

data.name: cmdcooldown_desc
data.value: Sets a cooldown per user for a command. Set it to 0 to remove the cooldown.

data.name: allcmdcooldowns_desc
data.value: Shows a list of all commands and their respective cooldowns.

data.name: addquote_desc
data.value: Adds a new quote with the specified name and message.

data.name: showquote_desc
data.value: Shows a random quote with a specified name.

data.name: searchquote_desc
data.value: Shows a random quote for a keyword that contains any text specified in the search.

data.name: quoteid_desc
data.value: Displays the quote with the specified ID number. Quote ID numbers can be found by typing `.liqu [num]` where `[num]` is a number of a page which contains 15 quotes.

data.name: deletequote_desc
data.value: Deletes a quote with the specified ID. You have to be either server Administrator or the creator of the quote to delete it.

data.name: draw_desc
data.value: Draws a card from the deck.If you supply number X, she draws up to 5 cards from the deck.

data.name: flip_desc
data.value: Flips coin(s) - heads or tails, and shows an image.

data.name: betflip_desc
data.value: Bet to guess will the result be heads or tails. Guessing awards you 1.95x the currency you've bet (rounded up). Multiplier can be changed by the bot owner.

data.name: roll_desc
data.value: Rolls 0-100. If you supply a number `X` it rolls up to 30 normal dice. If you split 2 numbers with letter `d` (`xdy`) it will roll `X` dice from 1 to `y`. `Y` can be a letter 'F' if you want to roll fate dice instead of dnd.

data.name: rolluo_desc
data.value: Rolls `X` normal dice (up to 30) unordered. If you split 2 numbers with letter `d` (`xdy`) it will roll `X` dice from 1 to `y`.

data.name: joinrace_desc
data.value: Joins a new race. You can specify an amount of currency for betting (optional). You will get YourBet*(participants-1) back if you win.

data.name: raffle_desc
data.value: Prints a name and ID of a random user from the online list from the (optional) role.

data.name: give_desc
data.value: Give someone a certain amount of currency.

data.name: award_desc
data.value: Awards someone a certain amount of currency. You can also specify a role name to award currency to all users in a role.

data.name: take_desc
data.value: Takes a certain amount of currency from someone.

data.name: betroll_desc
data.value: Bets a certain amount of currency and rolls a dice. Rolling over 66 yields x2 of your currency, over 90 - x4 and 100 x10.

data.name: trivia_desc
data.value: Starts a game of trivia. You can add `nohint` to prevent hints. First player to get to 10 points wins by default. You can specify a different number. 30 seconds per question.

data.name: tq_desc
data.value: Quits current trivia after current question.

data.name: typestop_desc
data.value: Stops a typing contest on the current channel.

data.name: typeadd_desc
data.value: Adds a new article to the typing contest.

data.name: poll_desc
data.value: Creates a poll which requires users to send the number of the voting option to the bot.

data.name: pollend_desc
data.value: Stops active poll on this server and prints the results in this channel.

data.name: pick_desc
data.value: Picks the currency planted in this channel. 60 seconds cooldown.

data.name: plant_desc
data.value: Spend an amount of currency to plant it in this channel. Default is 1. (If bot is restarted or crashes, the currency will be lost)

data.name: gencurrency_desc
data.value: Toggles currency generation on this channel. Every posted message will have chance to spawn currency. Chance is specified by the Bot Owner. (default is 2%)

data.name: leet_desc
data.value: Converts a text to leetspeak with 6 (1-6) severity levels

data.name: choose_desc
data.value: Chooses a thing from a list of things

data.name: rps_desc
data.value: Play a game of Rocket-Paperclip-Scissors with Nadeko.

data.name: next_desc
data.value: Goes to the next song in the queue. You have to be in the same voice channel as the bot. You can skip multiple songs, but in that case songs will not be requeued if {0}rcs or {0}rpl is enabled.

data.name: stop_desc
data.value: Stops the music and clears the playlist. Stays in the channel.

data.name: destroy_desc
data.value: Completely stops the music and unbinds the bot from the channel. (may cause weird behaviour)

data.name: queue_desc
data.value: Queue a song using keywords or a link. Bot will join your voice channel. **You must be in a voice channel**.

data.name: soundcloudqueue_desc
data.value: Queue a soundcloud song using keywords. Bot will join your voice channel. **You must be in a voice channel**.

data.name: listqueue_desc
data.value: Lists 15 currently queued songs per page. Default page is 1.

data.name: nowplaying_desc
data.value: Shows the song that the bot is currently playing.

data.name: defvol_desc
data.value: Sets the default music volume when music playback is started (0-100). Persists through restarts.

data.name: max_desc
data.value: Sets the music playback volume to 100%.

data.name: half_desc
data.value: Sets the music playback volume to 50%.

data.name: playlist_desc
data.value: Queues up to 500 songs from a youtube playlist specified by a link, or keywords.

data.name: soundcloudpl_desc
data.value: Queue a Soundcloud playlist using a link.

data.name: localpl_desc
data.value: Queues all songs from a directory.

data.name: radio_desc
data.value: Queues a radio stream from a link. It can be a direct mp3 radio stream, .m3u, .pls .asx or .xspf (Usage Video: <https://streamable.com/al54>)

data.name: local_desc
data.value: Queues a local file by specifying a full path.

data.name: move_desc
data.value: Moves the bot to your voice channel. (works only if music is already playing)

data.name: remove_desc
data.value: Remove a song by its # in the queue, or 'all' to remove whole queue.

data.name: movesong_desc
data.value: Moves a song from one position to another.

data.name: setmaxqueue_desc
data.value: Sets a maximum queue size. Supply 0 or no argument to have no limit.

data.name: repeatpl_desc
data.value: Toggles repeat of all songs in the queue (every song that finishes is added to the end of the queue).

data.name: save_desc
data.value: Saves a playlist under a certain name. Playlist name must be no longer than 20 characters and must not contain dashes.

data.name: load_desc
data.value: Loads a saved playlist using its ID. Use `{0}pls` to list all saved playlists and `{0}save` to save new ones.

data.name: playlists_desc
data.value: Lists all playlists. Paginated, 20 per page. Default page is 0.

data.name: deleteplaylist_desc
data.value: Deletes a saved playlist. Works only if you made it or if you are the bot owner.

data.name: goto_desc
data.value: Goes to a specific time in seconds in a song.

data.name: autoplay_desc
data.value: Toggles autoplay - When the song is finished, automatically queue a related Youtube song. (Works only for Youtube songs and when queue is empty)

data.name: lolchamp_desc
data.value: Shows League Of Legends champion statistics. If there are spaces/apostrophes or in the name - omit them. Optional second parameter is a role.

data.name: lolban_desc
data.value: Shows top banned champions ordered by ban rate.

data.name: hitbox_desc
data.value: Notifies this channel when a certain user starts streaming.

data.name: twitch_desc
data.value: Notifies this channel when a certain user starts streaming.

data.name: beam_desc
data.value: Notifies this channel when a certain user starts streaming.

data.name: removestream_desc
data.value: Removes notifications of a certain streamer from a certain platform on this channel.

data.name: liststreams_desc
data.value: Lists all streams you are following on this server.

data.name: convert_desc
data.value: Convert quantities. Use `{0}convertlist` to see supported dimensions and currencies.

data.name: convertlist_desc
data.value: List of the convertible dimensions and currencies.

data.name: wowjoke_desc
data.value: Get one of Kwoth's penultimate WoW jokes.

data.name: osu_desc
data.value: Shows osu stats for a player.

data.name: osub_desc
data.value: Shows information about an osu beatmap.

data.name: memelist_desc
data.value: Pulls a list of memes you can use with `{0}memegen` from http://memegen.link/templates/

data.name: memegen_desc
data.value: Generates a meme from memelist with top and bottom text.

data.name: weather_desc
data.value: Shows weather data for a specified city. You can also specify a country after a comma.

data.name: youtube_desc
data.value: Searches youtubes and shows the first result

data.name: anime_desc
data.value: Queries anilist for an anime and shows the first result.

data.name: imdb_desc
data.value: Queries omdb for movies or series, show first result.

data.name: manga_desc
data.value: Queries anilist for a manga and shows the first result.

data.name: image_desc
data.value: Pulls the first image found using a search parameter. Use `{0}rimg` for different results.

data.name: randomimage_desc
data.value: Pulls a random image using a search parameter.

data.name: google_desc
data.value: Get a Google search link for some terms.

data.name: hearthstone_desc
data.value: Searches for a Hearthstone card and shows its image. Takes a while to complete.

data.name: urbandict_desc
data.value: Searches Urban Dictionary for a word.

data.name: chucknorris_desc
data.value: Shows a random Chuck Norris joke from <http://api.icndb.com/jokes/random/>

data.name: magicitem_desc
data.value: Shows a random magic item from <https://1d4chan.org/wiki/List_of_/tg/%27s_magic_items>

data.name: revav_desc
data.value: Returns a Google reverse image search for someone's avatar.

data.name: revimg_desc
data.value: Returns a Google reverse image search for an image from a link.

data.name: safebooru_desc
data.value: Shows a random image from safebooru with a given tag. Tag is optional but preferred. (multiple tags are appended with +)

data.name: wiki_desc
data.value: Gives you back a wikipedia link

data.name: color_desc
data.value: Shows you what color corresponds to that hex.

data.name: videocall_desc
data.value: Creates a private <http://www.appear.in> video call link for you and other mentioned people. The link is sent to mentioned people via a private message.

data.name: hentai_desc
data.value: Shows a hentai image from a random website (gelbooru or danbooru or konachan or atfbooru or yandere) with a given tag. Tag is optional but preferred. Only 1 tag allowed.

data.name: danbooru_desc
data.value: Shows a random hentai image from danbooru with a given tag. Tag is optional but preferred. (multiple tags are appended with +)

data.name: atfbooru_desc
data.value: Shows a random hentai image from atfbooru with a given tag. Tag is optional but preferred.

data.name: gelbooru_desc
data.value: Shows a random hentai image from gelbooru with a given tag. Tag is optional but preferred. (multiple tags are appended with +)

data.name: rule34_desc
data.value: Shows a random image from rule34.xx with a given tag. Tag is optional but preferred. (multiple tags are appended with +)

data.name: e621_desc
data.value: Shows a random hentai image from e621.net with a given tag. Tag is optional but preferred. Use spaces for multiple tags.

data.name: cp_desc
data.value: We all know where this will lead you to.

data.name: createwar_desc
data.value: Creates a new war by specifying a size (>10 and multiple of 5) and enemy clan name.

data.name: startwar_desc
data.value: Starts a war with a given number.

data.name: listwar_desc
data.value: Shows the active war claims by a number. Shows all wars in a short way if no number is specified.

data.name: claim_desc
data.value: Claims a certain base from a certain war. You can supply a name in the third optional argument to claim in someone else's place.

data.name: claimfinish_desc
data.value: Finish your claim with 3 stars if you destroyed a base. First argument is the war number, optional second argument is a base number if you want to finish for someone else.

data.name: claimfinish2_desc
data.value: Finish your claim with 2 stars if you destroyed a base. First argument is the war number, optional second argument is a base number if you want to finish for someone else.

data.name: claimfinish1_desc
data.value: Finish your claim with 1 star if you destroyed a base. First argument is the war number, optional second argument is a base number if you want to finish for someone else.

data.name: unclaim_desc
data.value: Removes your claim from a certain war. Optional second argument denotes a person in whose place to unclaim

data.name: endwar_desc
data.value: Ends the war with a given index.

data.name: translate_desc
data.value: Translates from>to text. From the given language to the destination language.

data.name: translangs_desc
data.value: Lists the valid languages for translation.

data.name: guide_desc
data.value: Sends a readme and a guide links to the channel.

data.name: calcops_desc
data.value: Shows all available operations in the `{0}calc` command

data.name: delallquotes_desc
data.value: Deletes all quotes on a specified keyword.

data.name: greetdmmsg_desc
data.value: Sets a new join announcement message which will be sent to the user who joined. Type `%user%` if you want to mention the new member. Using it with no message will show the current DM greet message. You can use embed json from <http://nadekobot.me/embedbuilder/> instead of a regular text, if you want the message to be embedded.

data.name: cash_desc
data.value: Check how much currency a person has. (Defaults to yourself)

data.name: listperms_desc
data.value: Lists whole permission chain with their indexes. You can specify an optional page number if there are a lot of permissions.

data.name: allusrmdls_desc
data.value: Enable or disable all modules for a specific user.

data.name: moveperm_desc
data.value: Moves permission from one position to another in the Permissions list.

data.name: removeperm_desc
data.value: Removes a permission from a given position in the Permissions list.

data.name: migratedata_desc
data.value: Migrate data from old bot configuration

data.name: checkstream_desc
data.value: Checks if a user is online on a certain streaming platform.

data.name: showemojis_desc
data.value: Shows a name and a link to every SPECIAL emoji in the message.

data.name: showemojis_usage
data.value: `{0}se A message full of SPECIAL emojis`

data.name: shuffledeck_desc
data.value: Reshuffles all cards back into the deck.

data.name: forwardmessages_desc
data.value: Toggles forwarding of non-command messages sent to bot's DM to the bot owners

data.name: forwardtoall_desc
data.value: Toggles whether messages will be forwarded to all bot owners or only to the first one specified in the credentials.json file

data.name: resetpermissions_desc
data.value: Resets the bot's permissions module on this server to the default value.

data.name: antiraid_desc
data.value: Sets an anti-raid protection on the server. First argument is number of people which will trigger the protection. Second one is a time interval in which that number of people needs to join in order to trigger the protection, and third argument is punishment for those people (Kick, Ban, Mute)

data.name: antispam_desc
data.value: Stops people from repeating same message X times in a row. You can specify to either mute, kick or ban the offenders. Max message count is 10.

data.name: chatmute_desc
data.value: Prevents a mentioned user from chatting in text channels.

data.name: voicemute_desc
data.value: Prevents a mentioned user from speaking in voice channels.

data.name: konachan_desc
data.value: Shows a random hentai image from konachan with a given tag. Tag is optional but preferred.

data.name: setmuterole_desc
data.value: Sets a name of the role which will be assigned to people who should be muted. Default is nadeko-mute.

data.name: adsarm_desc
data.value: Toggles the automatic deletion of confirmations for `{0}iam` and `{0}iamn` commands.

data.name: setstream_desc
data.value: Sets the bots stream. First argument is the twitch link, second argument is stream name.

data.name: chatunmute_desc
data.value: Removes a mute role previously set on a mentioned user with `{0}chatmute` which prevented him from chatting in text channels.

data.name: unmute_desc
data.value: Unmutes a mentioned user previously muted with `{0}mute` command.

data.name: xkcd_desc
data.value: Shows a XKCD comic. No arguments will retrieve random one. Number argument will retrieve a specific comic, and "latest" will get the latest one.

data.name: placelist_desc
data.value: Shows the list of available tags for the `{0}place` command.

data.name: place_desc
data.value: Shows a placeholder image of a given tag. Use `{0}placelist` to see all available tags. You can specify the width and height of the image as the last two optional arguments.

data.name: togethertube_desc
data.value: Creates a new room on <https://togethertube.com> and shows the link in the chat.

data.name: publicpoll_desc
data.value: Creates a public poll which requires users to type a number of the voting option in the channel command is ran in.

data.name: autotranslang_desc
data.value: Sets your source and target language to be used with `{0}at`. Specify no arguments to remove previously set value.

data.name: autotranslate_desc
data.value: Starts automatic translation of all messages by users who set their `{0}atl` in this channel. You can set "del" argument to automatically delete all translated user messages.

data.name: listquotes_desc
data.value: Lists all quotes on the server ordered alphabetically. 15 Per page.

data.name: typedel_desc
data.value: Deletes a typing article given the ID.

data.name: typelist_desc
data.value: Lists added typing articles with their IDs. 15 per page.

data.name: listservers_desc
data.value: Lists servers the bot is on with some basic info. 15 per page.

data.name: hentaibomb_desc
data.value: Shows a total 5 images (from gelbooru, danbooru, konachan, yandere and atfbooru). Tag is optional but preferred.

data.name: cleverbot_desc
data.value: Toggles cleverbot session. When enabled, the bot will reply to messages starting with bot mention in the server. Custom reactions starting with %mention% won't work if cleverbot is enabled.

data.name: shorten_desc
data.value: Attempts to shorten an URL, if it fails, returns the input URL.

data.name: mcq_desc
data.value: Finds information about a minecraft server.

data.name: wikia_desc
data.value: Gives you back a wikia link

data.name: yandere_desc
data.value: Shows a random image from yandere with a given tag. Tag is optional but preferred. (multiple tags are appended with +)

data.name: magicthegathering_desc
data.value: Searches for a Magic The Gathering card.

data.name: yodify_desc
data.value: Translates your normal sentences into Yoda styled sentences!

data.name: attack_desc
data.value: Attacks a target with the given move. Use `{0}movelist` to see a list of moves your type can use.

data.name: heal_desc
data.value: Heals someone. Revives those who fainted. Costs a NadekoFlower.

data.name: movelist_desc
data.value: Lists the moves you are able to use

data.name: settype_desc
data.value: Set your poketype. Costs a NadekoFlower. Provide no arguments to see a list of available types.

data.name: type_desc
data.value: Get the poketype of the target.

data.name: hangmanlist_desc
data.value: Shows a list of hangman term types.

data.name: hangman_desc
data.value: Starts a game of hangman in the channel. Use `{0}hangmanlist` to see a list of available term types. Defaults to 'all'.

data.name: crstatsclear_desc
data.value: Resets the counters on `{0}crstats`. You can specify a trigger to clear stats only for that trigger.

data.name: crstats_desc
data.value: Shows a list of custom reactions and the number of times they have been executed. Paginated with 10 per page. Use `{0}crstatsclear` to reset the counters.

data.name: overwatch_desc
data.value: Show's basic stats on a player (competitive rank, playtime, level etc) Region codes are: `eu` `us` `cn` `kr`

data.name: acro_desc
data.value: Starts an Acrophobia game. Second argument is optional round length in seconds. (default is 60)

data.name: logevents_desc
data.value: Shows a list of all events you can subscribe to with `{0}log`

data.name: log_desc
data.value: Toggles logging event. Disables it if it is active anywhere on the server. Enables if it isn't active. Use `{0}logevents` to see a list of all events you can subscribe to.

data.name: fairplay_desc
data.value: Toggles fairplay. While enabled, the bot will prioritize songs from users who didn't have their song recently played instead of the song's position in the queue.

data.name: define_desc
data.value: Finds a definition of a word.

data.name: setmaxplaytime_desc
data.value: Sets a maximum number of seconds (>14) a song can run before being skipped automatically. Set 0 to have no limit.

data.name: autohentai_desc
data.value: Posts a hentai every X seconds with a random tag from the provided tags. Use `|` to separate tags. 20 seconds minimum. Provide no arguments to disable.

data.name: rotaterolecolor_desc
data.value: Rotates a roles color on an interval with a list of supplied colors. First argument is interval in seconds (Minimum 60). Second argument is a role, followed by a space-separated list of colors in hex. Provide a rolename with a 0 interval to disable.

data.name: createinvite_desc
data.value: Creates a new invite which has infinite max uses and never expires.

data.name: pollstats_desc
data.value: Shows the poll results without stopping the poll on this server.

data.name: repeatlist_desc
data.value: Shows currently repeating messages and their indexes.

data.name: repeatremove_desc
data.value: Removes a repeating message on a specified index. Use `{0}repeatlist` to see indexes.

data.name: antispamignore_desc
data.value: Toggles whether antispam ignores current channel. Antispam must be enabled.

data.name: cmdcosts_desc
data.value: Shows a list of command costs. Paginated with 9 commands per page.

data.name: commandcost_desc
data.value: Sets a price for a command. Running that command will take currency from users. Set 0 to remove the price.

data.name: startevent_desc
data.value: Starts one of the events seen on public nadeko.

data.name: slotstats_desc
data.value: Shows the total stats of the slot command for this bot's session.

data.name: slottest_desc
data.value: Tests to see how much slots payout for X number of plays.

data.name: slot_desc
data.value: Play Nadeko slots. Max bet is 9999. 1.5 second cooldown per user.

data.name: waifuclaimeraffinity_desc
data.value: Sets your affinity towards someone you want to be claimed by. Setting affinity will reduce their `{0}claim` on you by 20%. You can leave second argument empty to clear your affinity. 30 minutes cooldown.

data.name: waifuclaim_desc
data.value: Claim a waifu for yourself by spending currency. You must spend at least 10% more than her current value unless she set `{0}affinity` towards you.

data.name: divorce_desc
data.value: Releases your claim on a specific waifu. You will get some of the money you've spent back unless that waifu has an affinity towards you. 6 hours cooldown.

data.name: waifuinfo_desc
data.value: Shows waifu stats for a target person. Defaults to you if no user is provided.

data.name: mal_desc
data.value: Shows basic info from a MyAnimeList profile.

data.name: setmusicchannel_desc
data.value: Sets the current channel as the default music output channel. This will output playing, finished, paused and removed songs to that channel instead of the channel where the first song was queued in.

data.name: reloadimages_desc
data.value: Reloads images bot is using. Safe to use even when bot is being used heavily.

data.name: shardstats_desc
data.value: Stats for shards. Paginated with 25 shards per page.

data.name: connectshard_desc
data.value: Try (re)connecting a shard with a certain shardid when it dies. No one knows will it work. Keep an eye on the console for errors.

data.name: shardid_desc
data.value: Shows which shard is a certain guild on, by guildid.

data.name: tictactoe_desc
data.value: Starts a game of tic tac toe. Another user must run the command in the same channel in order to accept the challenge. Use numbers 1-9 to play. 15 seconds per move.

data.name: timezones_desc
data.value: List of all timezones available on the system to be used with `{0}timezone`.

data.name: timezone_desc
data.value: Sets this guilds timezone. This affects bot's time output in this server (logs, etc..)

data.name: languagesetdefault_desc
data.value: Sets the bot's default response language. All servers which use a default locale will use this one. Setting to `default` will use the host's current culture. Provide no arguments to see currently set language.

data.name: languageset_desc
data.value: Sets this server's response language. If bot's response strings have been translated to that language, bot will use that language in this server. Reset by using `default` as the locale name. Provide no arguments to see currently set language.

data.name: languageslist_desc
data.value: List of languages for which translation (or part of it) exist atm.

data.name: rategirl_desc
data.value: Use the universal hot-crazy wife zone matrix to determine the girl's worth. It is everything young men need to know about women. At any moment in time, any woman you have previously located on this chart can vanish from that location and appear anywhere else on the chart.

data.name: lucky7_desc
data.value: Bet currency on the game and start rolling 3 sided dice. At any point you can choose to [m]ove (roll again) or [s]tay (get the amount bet times the current multiplier).

data.name: vcrolelist_desc
data.value: Shows a list of currently set voice channel roles.

data.name: vcrole_desc
data.value: Sets or resets a role which will be given to users who join the voice channel you're in when you run this command. Provide no role name to disable. You must be in a voice channel to run this command.

data.name: crad_desc
data.value: Toggles whether the message triggering the custom reaction will be automatically deleted.

data.name: crdm_desc
data.value: Toggles whether the response message of the custom reaction will be sent as a direct message.

data.name: aliaslist_desc
data.value: Shows the list of currently set aliases. Paginated.

data.name: alias_desc
data.value: Create a custom alias for a certain Nadeko command. Provide no alias to remove the existing one.

data.name: alias_usage
data.value: `{0}alias allin $bf 100 h` or `{0}alias "linux thingy" >loonix Spyware Windows`

data.name: warnlog_desc
data.value: See a list of warnings of a certain user.

data.name: startupcommandadd_desc
data.value: Adds a command to the list of commands which will be executed automatically in the current channel, in the order they were added in, by the bot when it startups up.

data.name: startupcommandremove_desc
data.value: Removes a startup command with the provided command text.

data.name: startupcommands_desc
data.value: Lists all startup commands in the order they will be executed in.

data.name: unban_desc
data.value: Unbans a user with the provided user#discrim or id.

data.name: wait_desc
data.value: Used only as a startup command. Waits a certain number of miliseconds before continuing the execution of the following startup commands.

data.name: warnclear_desc
data.value: Clears all warnings from a certain user.

data.name: warnpunish_desc
data.value: Sets a punishment for a certain number of warnings. Provide no punishment to remove.

data.name: claimpatreonrewards_desc
data.value: Claim patreon rewards. If you're subscribed to bot owner's patreon you can use this command to claim your rewards - assuming bot owner did setup has their patreon key.

data.name: ping_desc
data.value: Ping the bot to see if there are latency issues.

data.name: slowmodewhitelist_desc
data.value: Ignores a role or a user from the slowmode feature.

data.name: time_desc
data.value: Shows the current time and timezone in the specified location.

data.name: patreonrewardsreload_desc
data.value: Forces the update of the list of patrons who are eligible for the reward.

data.name: shopadd_desc
data.value: Adds an item to the shop by specifying type price and name. Available types are role and list.

data.name: shopremove_desc
data.value: Removes an item from the shop by its ID.

data.name: shop_desc
data.value: Lists this server's administrators' shop. Paginated.

data.name: rolehoist_desc
data.value: Toggles if this role is displayed in the sidebar or not

data.name: buy_desc
data.value: Buys an item from the shop on a given index. If buying items, make sure that the bot can DM you.

data.name: gamevoicechannel_desc
data.value: Toggles game voice channel feature in the voice channel you're currently in. Users who join the game voice channel will get automatically redirected to the voice channel with the name of their current game, if it exists. Can't move users to channels that the bot has no connect permission for. One per server.

data.name: shoplistadd_desc
data.value: Adds an item to the list of items for sale in the shop entry given the index. You usually want to run this command in the secret channel, so that the unique items are not leaked.

data.name: gcmd_desc
data.value: Toggles whether a command can be used on any server.

data.name: gmod_desc
data.value: Toggles whether a module can be used on any server.

data.name: lgp_desc
data.value: Lists global permissions set by the bot owner.

data.name: resetglobalpermissions_desc
data.value: Resets global permissions set by bot owner.
